        Firebase Auth Guide
      </h1>
      <p class="text-text-secondary text-lg leading-relaxed">
        Firebase Authentication is Google's <strong class="text-white">free authentication service</strong>.
        It can be used for both web and mobile apps.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <Callout client:load variant="tip" title="Why Firebase Auth?" locale="en">
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mt-2">
          <li>Free tier: Unlimited MAU</li>
          <li>Social login support for Google, Facebook, Apple, etc.</li>
          <li>Email/password and phone number authentication</li>
          <li>Integration with other Firebase services (Firestore, Storage)</li>
          <li>Same API for mobile apps (Flutter, React Native)</li>
        </ul>
      </Callout>
    </section>

    <article class="prose prose-invert max-w-none">
      <!-- Step 1: Firebase Setup -->
